  <h2>Food Pairing Guide</h2>

<p>Prosecco's bright acidity, delicate bubbles, and clean mineral finish create natural <strong>flavor bridges</strong> with a remarkable range of dishes. The wine's effervescence cuts through rich textures while its crisp acidity enhances both salty and sweet flavors, making it one of the most versatile pairing wines in your cellar.</p>

<h3>Classic Venetian Pairings</h3>
<p>In its native Veneto region, Prosecco traditionally accompanies <strong>cicchetti</strong> (Venetian small plates). The wine's mineral backbone perfectly complements briny baccalà mantecato (whipped cod) and sarde in saor (sweet and sour sardines). These pairings work because the bubbles lift the fish oils while the wine's acidity balances the dishes' saltiness.</p>

<h3>Perfect Everyday Matches</h3>
<ul class="bg-wine-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
<li><strong>Prosciutto di Parma:</strong> The wine's effervescence cuts through the ham's fat while its fruit notes complement the meat's sweetness</li>
<li><strong>Fresh mozzarella with basil:</strong> Prosecco's clean minerality enhances the cheese's creaminess without overwhelming delicate flavors</li>
<li><strong>Fried calamari:</strong> The bubbles cleanse the palate between bites while acidity cuts through the oil</li>
<li><strong>Risotto ai funghi porcini:</strong> The wine's earthiness echoes the mushrooms while bubbles lighten the dish's richness</li>
<li><strong>Sushi and sashimi:</strong> Prosecco's delicate nature won't compete with raw fish, while its acidity enhances umami flavors</li>
</ul>

<h3>Special Occasion Selections</h3>
<p>For celebrations, pair <strong>Valdobbiadene DOCG</strong> with oysters Rockefeller—the wine's mineral complexity matches the brine while bubbles amplify the dish's luxury factor. <strong>Cartizze</strong>, with its touch of residual sugar, creates magical harmony with foie gras, where the wine's effervescence cuts the richness while its subtle sweetness complements the liver's intensity.</p>

<p class="text-wine-700">The key to successful Prosecco pairing lies in respecting its elegant restraint. Unlike Champagne's power or Cava's earthiness, Prosecco excels with lighter dishes where its clean, refreshing character can shine without overwhelming delicate flavors.</p>

